<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-04T03:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-04T03:35:00-05:00" n="250" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d250">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/523: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-04T12:00:00+03:25">May 4,
                                    1942—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received May 4—11:32 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>141. Both Shah and Prime Minister have requested me to express to
                            Department their hope that the arrival of the American advisers
                            requested will not be long delayed. They now wish to have three
                            additional advisers for finance and aviation and an army engineer. I
                            suggested that they make formal request for these advisers to the
                            Department through the Iranian Minister in Washington and the Prime
                            Minister stated he would do so.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>